                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 340</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Prime Minister of Norway, <persName>Einar Gerhardsen</persName>, paid his
                    first visit to the United States in May 1951. It was an informal, unofficial
                    visit in which he visited several Norwegian-American communities around the
                    country, going as far west as Seattle. He had expressed a desire to meet some
                    American labor leaders and was the guest of <persName corresp="#p_LJL1">John L.
                        Lewis</persName> at a small private luncheon in Washington on May 26.</p>
                <p>On Monday, May 28, the Prime Minister and Mrs. <persName>Gerhardsen</persName>
                    had lunch with the President. That same afternoon
                        <persName>Gerhardsen</persName> and the Norwegian Ambassador to the United
                    States met with the Secretary of State. A memorandum of their conversation and
                    other information on <persName>Gerhardsen</persName>’s trip is in Secretary’s
                    Memoranda, lot 53D444.</p>
            </div>
